Class Movie

java.lang.Object
Movie
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Movie extends Object implements Serializable
This class represents a Movie object with various attributes such as year, title, duration, genres, rating, score, director, and actors. It implements the Serializable interface to allow objects of this class to be serialized and deserialized.

      title - The title of the movie.

      score - The score of the movie.
      director - The director of the movie.
      actor1 - The first actor of the movie.

      BadYearException - If the provided year is invalid.
      BadTitleException - If the provided title is empty or null.
      BadDurationException - If the provided duration is invalid.
      BadGenreException - If the provided genre is invalid.

      BadNameException - If the provided director or actor names are empty or null.
